MORNING REPORT: GRAMMY WATCH 
Bette and Stevie Sing at Grammys: Bette Midler, Stevie Wonder and the 
Eurythmics' David Stewart were added Tuesday to the roster appearing on the 
32nd Annual Grammy Awards show on CBS tonight at 8. 
Midler, a nominee for record of the year and best female pop vocal performance, 
will perform "Wind Beneath My Wings." Wonder, a 17-time Grammy winner, will 
sing "We Can Work It Out" as part of the special tribute to Paul McCartney. 
Stewart will be a presenter during the delayed telecast. BETH KLEID 
